    return `<section class="section v151-section accent" id="v151-page-language-selector"><div class="container section-head"><div><div class="eyebrow">v1.51 preferred-language page selector</div><h2>Let users read key pages with support in 100+ major languages — then return to Legal English.</h2></div><p>Students should be able to understand the homepage, dashboard steps, SmartTeacher AI, course placement, homework, class links, scheduling, billing, certificates, and support instructions in their preferred language when needed. The goal still stays Legal English performance.</p></div><div class="container grid cols-2"><article class="panel v151-selector-card"><h3>Choose preferred explanation language</h3><p class="muted">This is a learning bridge for platform pages and class materials, not a certified translation promise.</p><select class="input js-v151-language-select" aria-label="Preferred explanation language">${v151LanguageOptions()}</select><div class="tag-row"><button class="btn gold js-v151-save-language">Save preferred language</button><button class="btn teal js-v151-explain-page">Explain this page</button><button class="btn light js-v151-continuity">Run preservation check</button></div><p class="notice"><strong>Safe boundary:</strong> native-language page help is learning support only. It is not legal advice, certified translation, court interpretation, final legal meaning, or a substitute for teacher/professional review.</p></article><article class="panel"><h3>What this lets students do</h3><ul class="feature-list">${v151Enabled.map(item=>`<li>${escapeHtml(item)}</li>`).join('')}</ul></article></div><div class="container v151-mode-strip">${v151Modes.map(m=>`<span>${escapeHtml(m)}</span>`).join('')}</div><div class="container panel"><div class="panel-head"><div><h3>Recent page explanations</h3><p class="muted">Every explanation keeps the original English visible and points back to Legal English practice.</p></div><span class="status green">${v151MajorLanguages.length} major language options</span></div><div class="table-wrap"><table class="table"><tr><th>Page</th><th>Language</th><th>Created</th><th>Back-to-English step</th></tr>${v151Rows()}</table></div><p class="clean-note"><strong>Staff rule:</strong> rare, unsupported, low-confidence, sensitive, court/certified, or high-stakes legal/business language should route to teacher/staff/professional review instead of being presented as final translation.</p></div></section>`;
